<br>
Simple as that.  I have started soloing these easy things at 55, but I think the 51 earth pet would be good and this camp do able at level 51.  Safe xp as I have never had an add from a dryad, but the animals sometimes aggro me when I am sitting (if a level 51 could post on the aggro situation it would be nice).  <br>
<br>
Loot is not good, but not bad also.  Their loc is along the west wall in between the BB tunnel and the 'town'.  They appear as a fire (either blue or orange) next to trees.  Walk by them to get them to spawn.  The gnolls are also fun, but the dryads are eaiser. <br>
<br>
Let me know what you think.  I am on Xev, feel free to send a tell. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uliffthemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liff the Mage</A> at: 10/4/02 1:28:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=canelin>Canelin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(10/4/02 9:56:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=282.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Dryads</span><hr size=1> I hunted Dryads recently - see my post <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showMessage?topicID=276.topic">here.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
